Vermilyea Avenue, west side, north from and including West 204th Street (formerly Hawthorne Street). Beyond the apartment house on the N.W. corner of 204th Street, a building itself less than two years old at the time of this picture, construction of the northern wing of Piccadilly Garsen, 116-28 Vermilyea Avenue, is
going on.
October 26, 1927.
P. L. Sperr.
